The article is a consolidated report sent by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the House of Representatives. It provides an overview of military operations conducted by the United States Armed Forces in support of counterterrorism efforts and other objectives. The report includes information on deployments, operations, and support provided in various regions, including Afghanistan, Iraq and Syria, the Arabian Peninsula, Jordan, Lebanon, Turkey, East Africa, the Lake Chad Basin and Sahel Region, Cuba, the Philippines, Egypt, Kosovo, and North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) countries in Europe. The President emphasizes that these actions are carried out within the framework of his constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive, and that regular communication with Congress is maintained regarding these deployments.